	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In fact it's true both loopy's doc and my doc overcomplicate the thing.
<br />
<br />All you have to know is that $2005 affect the scroll and that $2006 affect the adress. However, $2005/2 doesn't work during rendering (only $2005/1 takes effect).
<br />When you affect the adress during rendering, it will take effect and the next tiles will be fetched at the specified location effectively "affecting" the scrolling  (also it's ORed with $2000, preventing it to fetch from pattern tables).
<br />
<br />However you can't deal with fine scrolls that way, therefore the need to mix $2005 and $2006 writes if you want to deal with fine scroll (which is absolutely not requirede if you DON'T deal with fine scrolls, which people seems not to understand by looping at loopy's docs.).
<br />
<br />I guess I just summed all just above without any complex diagrams. I'll probably have to edit my doc to make it simpler to understand for newcomers.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
